<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.3311/15.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chinese Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-09-12"><hi rend="italic">September 12,
                                    1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President desires to see Admiral Ching at 2.30 Thursday afternoon
                            instead of 5. Will you kindly so arrange the admiral’s program?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington
                            Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>